Virginia Tech, a renowned technical university, offers degrees in computer science, agriculture, engineering, and business.
Founded in 1872 as a land-grant school, it is a hub for research in biotechnology, energy, and fuel-cell technology.
The campus was rocked by a tragic shooting incident, resulting in the deaths of 32 individuals.
President George W. Bush attended a memorial service to honor the victims.
Classes were canceled for the week as the nation mourned the senseless violence.
The community, along with the entire nation, grieved the loss and reflected on the tragedy at Virginia Tech.
